title: High Tide
description: A beautiful young woman visits with the detectives and ends up dazzling the men, resulting in some fights as well as a few deaths along the way.

title: Local Girl
description: Darcy Peyton, a gangster's girlfriend, has stolen an envelope full of cash from her boyfriend. She plans to return to her small hometown and flaunt her newfound "wealth" in the faces of all the locals--especially her nasty redneck father--who mistreated her years before. She hires Kenny as her bodyguard, knowing that her ex-boyfriend will send some of his men after her to get the money back.

title: Bride and Seek
description: Dave Thorne is hired by Nancy Anders to find her missing husband. She is the former Nancy Clayborne of New York and her family is very wealthy. Her grandmother is a domineering woman who disapproved of her marrying Frank Anders so the two were forced to elope. Mrs. Clayborne believes that Anders is just a grifter out for her money but Nancy doesn't believe this. Arnie Helman and Stan Ritchie, two dangerous men also happen to be looking for Anders and they're not afraid to rough up anybody who gets in their way. Thorne will have to figure out who everybody is and what their part in this mystery is in order to solve it.

title: Little Mister Kelly
description: Boxer Hank Kelly's sparing partner is murdered and now someone is after his little son.

title: Prescription for Panic
description: When the patient of a female psychiatrist is gunned down for no apparent reason, Sandy Winfield decides to investigate.

title: The Quarterback
description: A gambler has convinced a young quarterback who is set to star in the Orange Bowl that his brother, a policeman, is taking bribes, and if he doesn't throw the game his brother will be exposed. The detectives set out to thwart the gambler's plans.

title: The Green Beret
description: Dave Thorne, a guerrilla warfare expert, is asked by the army to help train a Special Forces team--and to discover the enemy agent the army believes is on the team.

title: Elegy for a Bookkeeper
description: On his last day in prison, a bookkeeper suddenly dies--suspiciously, just before he was to give Ken evidence about the mob boss responsible for his being imprisoned. The dead man's daughter agrees to help Ken find the evidence he needs to bring the gangster to justice.

title: Green Bay Riddle
description: In the exclusive community of Green Bay a murder trial is in session. Charles Allen, a man who married into the community, is accused of murdering his father-in-law even though a body was never found. He is found not guilty but many still believe him to be...including his brother-in-law Richard Linden. Allen's wife travels to Miami and hires Ken Madison to prove once and for all her husband's innocence and find out who killed her father or what else may have happened to him.

title: Love Song for a Deadly Redhead
Masquerade
description: Dave goes undercover at a circus to discover why an accident during a performance has resulted in tensions rising among the circus' European members.
